Uniform exact family:
  m>=1
  incoming total H=2m-1
  a=(alpha,beta)=(0,m)
  b=(alpha,beta)=(m,0)
  z=0
  T_(a,b;H)-T_(b,a;H)=-I_(2m)

Therefore the same-sign signed and unsigned local defects have rank 2m.
The diagnostic's rank-ten witnesses are the m=5 member of this family.

Uniform unsigned orientation:
  L(c,d)=max(beta_c,beta_d-(alpha_c-beta_c))
  T_(a,b;H)-T_(b',a';H) is entrywise nonnegative if L(a,b)<L(b',a'),
  zero if the thresholds agree, and entrywise nonpositive if the first
  threshold is larger.

The zero mixed-sign count and zero threshold-orientation-failure count are
regression checks for this exact lemma.  The nonzero delta and determinant
failure counts rule out those two simpler orientation classifiers.

The zero scheduling-tie-classification count independently checks the
three exact equality cases in Lemma 22F3A23 throughout the displayed local
domain.  The lemma itself is proved uniformly; this is only its regression
test.
